      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the existing decision table into a new temporary table `J09B_temp`, keeping only rows where the tour starts with `\\\"J09B\\\"` (“Copy decision table into table J09B_temp where the tour starts with J09B”).\\n\\n2. In `J09B_temp`, add a new column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` (“Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column”).\\n\\n3. In `J09B_temp`, classify meter reading type by setting `ENTSCHEIDUNG` per these rules (apply in numeric order 1–5; later rules override earlier ones if they conflict):\\n   1. Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `\\\"KSA\\\"` when a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`. ELSE set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `\\\"EVU\\\"`.\\n   2. Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` of `0` to `\\\"EVU\\\"`.\\n   3. Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` 500–599 to `\\\"EVU\\\"`.\\n   4. Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` 900–999 to `\\\"EVU\\\"`.\\n   5. Set all houses with address area `Wiblingwerde` or `Breckerfeld` to `\\\"EVU\\\"`.\\n\\n4. Join `J09B_temp` with table `EABLG` using the `INSTALLATION` field as the join key (“JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION”).\\n\\n5. Join the result with tables `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using `EQUNR` as the join key, as specified: “JOIN table with NET_MASTER and SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR”.\\n\\n6. For the joined records, compare the customer data coming from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` (e.g. names, addresses, `EMAIL`) to determine where sales customer data is present or missing.\\n\\n7. Decide which customer data source to use (XOR gateway converted to if–else):\\n   If the joined `SALES_MASTER` data for the records to be exported is not empty:\\n   - Use sales customer data table entries:\\n     - For all records, fill the customer-related columns (`TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`) from `SALES_MASTER`.\\n   Else:\\n   - Use net data customer table entries:\\n     - For all records, fill these customer-related columns (`TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`) from `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n8. From the resulting final table, export the data as a CSV file named `J09B`. Use this column names, when exporting the file:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n\\n9. Send email with the CSV file to EVU using the following details (“Send email with the CSV file to EVU” and its annotation):\\n   - Email address `meter.readings@evu.com`\\n   - `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>` (replace the placeholder with the actual path of the exported `J09B` CSV file)\\n\\n10. After the email has been sent, delete the temporary table `J09B_temp` (“Delete temporary table”).\"}",
            "id": "lc_acbb4f12-2660-4ef8-94e6-0d507ace2ab8"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "1d4bf00b-96c5-47ee-a684-9ea32095366a",
        "tool_call_id": "call_SvekaVdKZhex4r07W1CAd83T",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the existing decision table into a new temporary table `J09B_temp`, keeping only rows where the tour starts with `\"J09B\"` (“Copy decision table into table J09B_temp where the tour starts with J09B”).\n\n2. In `J09B_temp`, add a new column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` (“Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column”).\n\n3. In `J09B_temp`, classify meter reading type by setting `ENTSCHEIDUNG` per these rules (apply in numeric order 1–5; later rules override earlier ones if they conflict):\n   1. Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `\"KSA\"` when a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`. ELSE set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `\"EVU\"`.\n   2. Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` of `0` to `\"EVU\"`.\n   3. Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` 500–599 to `\"EVU\"`.\n   4. Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` 900–999 to `\"EVU\"`.\n   5. Set all houses with address area `Wiblingwerde` or `Breckerfeld` to `\"EVU\"`.\n\n4. Join `J09B_temp` with table `EABLG` using the `INSTALLATION` field as the join key (“JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION”).\n\n5. Join the result with tables `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using `EQUNR` as the join key, as specified: “JOIN table with NET_MASTER and SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR”.\n\n6. For the joined records, compare the customer data coming from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` (e.g. names, addresses, `EMAIL`) to determine where sales customer data is present or missing.\n\n7. Decide which customer data source to use (XOR gateway converted to if–else):\n   If the joined `SALES_MASTER` data for the records to be exported is not empty:\n   - Use sales customer data table entries:\n     - For all records, fill the customer-related columns (`TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`) from `SALES_MASTER`.\n   Else:\n   - Use net data customer table entries:\n     - For all records, fill these customer-related columns (`TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`) from `NET_MASTER`.\n\n8. From the resulting final table, export the data as a CSV file named `J09B`. Use this column names, when exporting the file:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n\n9. Send email with the CSV file to EVU using the following details (“Send email with the CSV file to EVU” and its annotation):\n   - Email address `meter.readings@evu.com`\n   - `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>` (replace the placeholder with the actual path of the exported `J09B` CSV file)\n\n10. After the email has been sent, delete the temporary table `J09B_temp` (“Delete temporary table”)."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
